Subbarao Says ‘Above a Threshold’ Inflation Rise Unacceptable

-- B y   D r e w   B e n s o n
-- 
2011-09-26T16:40:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/subbarao-says-above-a-threshold-inflation-rise-unacceptable.html
Reserve Bank of India Governor
Duvvuri Subbarao said “above a threshold, you can’t accept high
inflation to have higher growth.”  The Indian inflation threshold is about 4 percent to 5
percent, he said today at an event in  New York , adding that
price pressures have been “fairly stubborn.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Drew Benson in Buenos Aires at 
 abenson9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Costelloe at 
 kcostelloe@bloomberg.net  